build a Turing Machine that halts on an binary string that is divisible by 4 (last two symbols are 0):

Q: set of states
Σ: input alphabet
Γ: tape alphabet (finite tape)
Σ ⊆ Γ & ∃ ⊔ ϵ Γ \ Σ
δ: Q x Γ -> Q x Γ x {L,R}
q0: start state
qA: accept state
qR: reject state

->Σ = {0,1}
->L = {w ϵ Σ* | w is even}
